                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Nope. They'll still eat 33% of the xp. Same as always. If your groups were doing &lt;50% of the damage before then I guess there's a chance you'll see upto 17% faster xp but I doubt it. More than likely, there will be no noticable change in xp accompanying the obvious reduction in dps.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Why oh why does nobody understand how the 33% rule works.
<br />

<br />
The pet eats 33% of the share of damage it does in XP, if it does less than 100% of the damage to the mob.
<br />

<br />
Assuming 'free' pulls, this basically reduces pet DPS by 33% for XP purposes.  Given that pulls aren't free, it is worse than this.  For purposes of quest/cash/success, it is better than this.
<br />

<br />
Basically, if our pets are doing 150 DPS, they are only 'worth' 100 DPS xp-wise.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
