                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A few problems with parsing:
<br />

<br />
1.  Not all parses calculate the same way (some start at beginning of fight and end when target is dead, some start at beginning of atk and end of atk).  In this light, the term "DPS" is somewhat ethereal, debateable to be sure.
<br />

<br />
2.  Pets which proc a dot do not have that damage taken into account while charmed (you can't see DoT damage in the game other than what you do or what you take).  Same goes with pet DD - a longtime problem for beastlords trying to determine pet dps.
<br />

<br />
3.  It would appear (I haven't reviewed logs to determine it) that innate mob delay in OoW seems to be better when uncharmed than while charmed. 
<br />

<br />
Even if we agree on one method to standardize a DPS calculation, it is clear that SoE is comparing us against other classes (Brenlo response on charming).  If this is true, the charm implementation is due to SoE seeking "class balance".  
<br />

<br />
As the robot said, "DANGER WILL ROBINSON!"  
<br />

<br />
This places us on the defensive, as SoE can claim that any adjustment to charm as implemented requires balancing to other classes.  Essentially, it's a lot like trying to prove a negative (e.g. Prove Sadam didn't plan to acquire nuclear weapons).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Nokei Orhaste</a></span>
<br />
Coercer for <span style="color: blue"><a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">House of Aegis</a></span>
<br />
Luclin
<br />
&lt;Retiring 11/02/04&gt;
<br />

<br />
E66.191/L h++ 2.8khp 4.6km ft12 BK10
<br />

<br />
It`s never fun until the druid dies.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
